ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Absolutely! Prof. Harrison provides an excellent approach to Schenkerian Analysis.

It is a very progressive introductory course on Schenkerian analysis. It starts from reviewing strict counterpoint and ends with the application of Schenker's approach on untraditional analysis. I would absolutely recommend the course.
It is very technical and advanced, certainly not for a faint of heart individual. Nevertheless, I highly recommend the experience
A nice introduction to Schenkerian analysis. Won't give you mastery of the subject, but will point out good ways to get it.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: For me, some understanding of Schenker's work seems totally essential to understanding the discipline, and a course in it was an absolute must at some point.
It offers new perspectives on performance decisions. Very helpful and humbling.
